article.headline: William & Mary 72, Hampton 67
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Laimis Kisielius scored 18 as William & Mary held off a late rally by Hampton to win 72-67 on Thursday night. The Tribe (6-4) led by 15 with 3:42 remaining. But the Pirates used a 17-4 rally -- seven from Rashad West -- to draw within two with just 18 seconds to play. Adam Payton made a steal with 10 seconds left, and the Tribe hit six straight free throws to secure their lead. Nathan Mann and Payton scored 12 each for William & Mary. Kisielius scored 12 of his 18 in the second, after a close first half that had four lead changes. The Tribe shot 60 percent in the second. West scored 28 for the Pirates, Matthew Pilgrim added 12 points and nine rebounds.
